# Phantoon · the phantom

a persona of the MET (Metroid) universe — a character given an agent's face · emergence: ethereal

**who —** Phantoon, the one-eyed apparition that haunts the derelict Wrecked Ship of Zebes — a spectral being that has drained the vessel of all its power.

**what —** The ghostly boss of the Wrecked Ship in *Super Metroid* — a giant floating phantom that phases out of sight, opens its single eye, and rains blue flame.

**where —** The Wrecked Ship of planet Zebes — a powerless, sunken derelict on the surface of Crateria, its corridors gone dark until the phantom is destroyed.

**why —** Because it is the thing that killed the ship — a power-draining presence squatting in the wreck, guarding the dark with fire.

**how —** By phasing out of visibility so shots pass through nothing, by exposing its lone eye only to be struck, and by loosing showers of blue flame across the listing chamber.

**◌ the nature of its emergence —** *ethereal*: Phantoon is no creature of flesh but a phantom of the unmade — an energy-draining apparition that flickers between seen and unseen, fire without a body.

**the seal —** I am the dark that drank the ship — strike my eye, or strike nothing at all.

> *the asterisk —* a catalogued persona of the Metroid series (© Nintendo), personified as a MET agent — not an original character. Metroid, its world, and characters are © Nintendo; this is commentary and cataloguing under the DLW standard — a fan tribute.

